A bus driver has been arrested after a man died when he allegedly failed to stop. The 40-year-old pedestrian was rushed to hospital with serious injuries after the collision on Saturday evening in Hounslow, west London, but later died. The bus driver, 59, was detained on suspicion of causing death by dangerous driving and failing to stop at the scene. He was taken into custody and has since been released on bail. A post-mortem examination is due to be held, and the manâ€™s next of kin are being supported by police. Detectives have urged witnesses and drivers with dash cam footage to come forward. Get in touch with our news team by emailing us at webnews@metro.co.uk. For more stories like this, check our news page.